{"id":4163,"date":"2020-09-30T07:23:57","date_gmt":"2020-09-30T07:23:57","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/cmhammar.skapaweb6.tripnet.se\/?page_id=4163"},"modified":"2024-10-21T08:53:16","modified_gmt":"2024-10-21T07:53:16","slug":"special-applications","status":"publish","type":"page","link":"https:\/\/www.cmhammar.com\/special-applications\/","title":{"rendered":"Special Applications"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<h1>\n\t\tSPECIAL APPLICATIONS\n\t<\/h1>\n\t<p>By combining, adapting, and developing technology, Hammar&#8217;s products are applicable to more areas for saving lives at sea.<\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n\t\t\t\t<img decoding=\"async\" data-src=\"https:\/\/www.cmhammar.com\/wp-content\/plugins\/bb-plugin\/img\/pixel.png\" alt=\"\" itemprop=\"image\" onerror=\"this.style.display='none'\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB3aWR0aD0iMSIgaGVpZ2h0PSIxIiB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciPjwvc3ZnPg==\" class=\"lazyload\" style=\"--smush-placeholder-width: 3px; --smush-placeholder-aspect-ratio: 3\/2;\" \/>\n<h3>\n\t\tHAMMAR IN SPECIAL APPLICATIONS\n\t<\/h3>\n\t<p>We continuously develop state-of-the-art products that correspond to our customers&#8217; demands. In collaboration with our customers, we design new products by unconventional and innovative thinking &#8211; products that increase safety at sea due to ingenuity and top-quality production. Hammar has a broad portfolio of components, and many are possible to combine in a new arrangement to solve your problem.<\/p>\n<h3>\n\t\tPRODUCTS ADAPTED FOR POLAR CLIMATE\n\t<\/h3>\n\t<p>The <a href=\"https:\/\/www.imo.org\/en\/MediaCentre\/HotTopics\/Pages\/Polar-default.aspx\">IMO Polar Code<\/a> sets increased focus on the capabilities of LSA (Life-Saving Appliances) onboard ships that operate in polar waters. For vessels complying with these standards, Hammar has developed the Polar Box to acquire a habitable climate for our Hammar H20 HRUs (Hydrostatic Release Units) to operate in. The Polar Box is a heated box designed to offer a float-free function to the H20 HRUs down to minus 50 degrees Celsius.<\/p>\n\t\t\t\t<img decoding=\"async\" data-src=\"https:\/\/www.cmhammar.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/polar-code.jpg\" alt=\"polar code\" itemprop=\"image\" height=\"366\" width=\"681\" title=\"polar code\" onerror=\"this.style.display='none'\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB3aWR0aD0iMSIgaGVpZ2h0PSIxIiB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciPjwvc3ZnPg==\" class=\"lazyload\" style=\"--smush-placeholder-width: 681px; --smush-placeholder-aspect-ratio: 681\/366;\" \/>\n<h3>\n\t\tTHE POLAR CODE\n\t<\/h3>\n\t<p>International Code for Ships Operating in Polar Waters &#8211; <a href=\"https:\/\/www.imo.org\/en\/MediaCentre\/HotTopics\/Pages\/polar-default.aspx\">The Polar Code<\/a> &#8211; is legislation adopted by the <a href=\"https:\/\/www.imo.org\/en\">IMO<\/a> under the <a href=\"https:\/\/www.imo.org\/en\/About\/Conventions\/Pages\/International-Convention-for-the-Safety-of-Life-at-Sea-(SOLAS),-1974.aspx\">SOLAS<\/a> and <a href=\"https:\/\/www.imo.org\/en\/About\/Conventions\/Pages\/International-Convention-for-the-Prevention-of-Pollution-from-Ships-(MARPOL).aspx\">MARPOL<\/a> to control design, construction, equipment training, and SAR (Search And Rescue) for ships operating the waters around the North and South Pole.<\/p>\n<p>The code was developed to protect the environment and people in these remote parts of the world. It came into force 1st of January 2017.<\/p>\n\t\t\t\t<img decoding=\"async\" data-src=\"https:\/\/www.cmhammar.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/Viking-Polar-box-1024x708.jpg\" alt=\"Viking Polar box\" itemprop=\"image\" height=\"708\" width=\"1024\" title=\"Viking Polar box\" onerror=\"this.style.display='none'\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB3aWR0aD0iMSIgaGVpZ2h0PSIxIiB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciPjwvc3ZnPg==\" class=\"lazyload\" style=\"--smush-placeholder-width: 1024px; --smush-placeholder-aspect-ratio: 1024\/708;\" \/>\n<h3>\n\t\tOUR SOLUTION\n\t<\/h3>\n\t<p>The Polar Box is developed to maintain the operatable environment (-30 to +65 degrees Celcius) for the Hammar H20 HRUs, even in the most severe cold temperature. The Polar Box may be equipped with one or two HRUs (Hydrostatic Release Units) or ERUs (Electronic Release Units).<\/p>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/www.cmhammar.com\/product-category\/polar-box\/\">Here you can find our range of Polar Boxes.<\/a><\/p>\n\t<a href=\"#modal1012683892\" data-toggle=\"modal\">\n    Learn more      <\/a>\n\t\t\t\t                          <h2>THE POLAR BOX<\/h2>\n                                <p><a href=\"https:\/\/www.cmhammar.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/12\/New-Image-scaled.jpg\"><img decoding=\"async\" data-src=\"https:\/\/www.cmhammar.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/12\/New-Image-scaled.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"2560\" height=\"1731\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB3aWR0aD0iMSIgaGVpZ2h0PSIxIiB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciPjwvc3ZnPg==\" class=\"lazyload\" style=\"--smush-placeholder-width: 2560px; --smush-placeholder-aspect-ratio: 2560\/1731;\" \/><\/a>The Polar Box is developed to maintain the operatable environment (-30 to +65 degrees Celcius) for the Hammar H20 HRUs, even in the most severe cold temperature. The Polar Box covers the H20 units in a protective shell equipped with a silicone rubber-coated heater element and a built-in temperature sensor. The heated Polar Box is insulated with PE foam on the inside of the front and backside to reduce heat leakage to the surroundings.Note that the Polar Box has several air outlet holes at the top of the box to allow quick access to water for the HRU. The heater element and its cable are fully protected against water and humidity.<h2>The HeaterGuard<\/h2>The heater element is connected to a HeaterGuard temperature control unit placed in a suitable heated space. The HeaterGuard&#8217;s mission is to maintain a set maximum temperature in the Polar Box. The system has an alarm output that is activated if any of the following fault conditions occur:<ul><li> Power failure on the power supply or blown fuse<\/li><li> Low temperature in the heater or open sensor circuit<\/li><li> High temperature in the heater or short circuit in the sensor circuit<\/li><li> Heater not responding or heater circuit broken<\/li><\/ul><h2>How to choose a Polar Box<\/h2>Hammar&#8217;s Polar Box is available in a range of varieties:<ul><li aria-level=\"1\"><b>Heated for one or two H20 units<\/b><\/li><\/ul>If your liferaft is equipped with a heating blanket, you may choose an option with one H20 unit cutting the cable and one H20 unit cutting the lashing.<ul><li aria-level=\"1\"><b>HRUs or ERUs<\/b><\/li><\/ul>The Polar Box can be arranged around the ERU (Electronic Release Unit) in an ERRS (Electronic Remote Release System) or with an HRU (Hydrostatic Release Unit).<ul><li aria-level=\"1\"><b>EX environment<\/b><\/li><\/ul><a href=\"https:\/\/www.cmhammar.com\/product-category\/polar-box\/\">Here you can find our range of Polar Boxes.<\/a><\/p>                              \n <h3>\n\t\tHAMMAR COR TECHNOLOGY\n\t<\/h3>\n\t<p>The Hammar COR Electronic Inflator System is a new patented technology. It can be customized after specific requirements and optimized for different applications. The technology creates a rapid and reliable activation of the PFD (Personal Flotation Device), even under extreme conditions.<\/p>\n<p>A complete Hammar COR system consists of a battery-powered Electric Control Unit (ECU) connected to an adaptor by a cable and a cylinder assembly with a CO2 cylinder glued to the piercing unit.<\/p>\n\t\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.cmhammar.com\/lifejacket-inflators\/#cor-technology\" target=\"_self\" rel=\"noopener\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\tRead more\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/a>\n<h3>\n\t\tHAMMAR COR IN  APPLICATIONS\n\t<\/h3>\n\t\t\t\t<img decoding=\"async\" data-src=\"https:\/\/www.cmhammar.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/02\/mustang3-1.jpg\" alt=\"mustang3\" itemprop=\"image\" height=\"631\" width=\"641\" title=\"mustang3\" onerror=\"this.style.display='none'\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB3aWR0aD0iMSIgaGVpZ2h0PSIxIiB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciPjwvc3ZnPg==\" class=\"lazyload\" style=\"--smush-placeholder-width: 641px; --smush-placeholder-aspect-ratio: 641\/631;\" \/>\n<h3>\n\t\tMUSTANG SURVIVAL&#8217;S RATIS LPU\n\t<\/h3>\n\t<p>The &#8220;first to market&#8221; application of the Hammar COR system is the life-preserving Unit RATIS from Mustang Survival. It was developed for special forces with high demand for an inflator system where activation could be adjusted depending on the mission.<\/p>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/mustangsurvival.ca\/blogs\/blog\/inflatable-innovation?_pos=1&amp;_sid=16b72e3bc&amp;_ss=r\">Visit Mustang Survival for more information<\/a>.<\/p>\n\t\t\t\t<img decoding=\"async\" data-src=\"https:\/\/www.cmhammar.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/02\/kraka.jpg\" alt=\"kraka\" itemprop=\"image\" height=\"625\" width=\"804\" title=\"kraka\" onerror=\"this.style.display='none'\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB3aWR0aD0iMSIgaGVpZ2h0PSIxIiB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciPjwvc3ZnPg==\" class=\"lazyload\" style=\"--smush-placeholder-width: 804px; --smush-placeholder-aspect-ratio: 804\/625;\" \/>\n<h3>\n\t\tKRAKA BOARD\n\t<\/h3>\n\t<p>Kraka Board is an inflatable platform for shallow water SAR (Search And Rescue) and situations where silence, low profile, and agility are crucial for a mission&#8217;s success. Kraka uses the COR ECU to reinflate the platform while cacheing. COR adds functionality if presenting inflation based on time or depth.<\/p>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/soalmarine.se\/kraka\/\">Visit Kraka Board for more information.<\/a><\/p>\n\t\t\t\t<img decoding=\"async\" data-src=\"https:\/\/www.cmhammar.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/02\/High-Eye-Maritime-2-1024x683.jpg\" alt=\"High-Eye-Maritime-2\" itemprop=\"image\" title=\"High-Eye-Maritime-2\" onerror=\"this.style.display='none'\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB3aWR0aD0iMSIgaGVpZ2h0PSIxIiB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciPjwvc3ZnPg==\" class=\"lazyload\" style=\"--smush-placeholder-width: 1024px; --smush-placeholder-aspect-ratio: 1024\/683;\" \/>\n<h3>\n\t\tPROTECTION OF VALUABLE EQUIPMENT\n\t<\/h3>\n\t<p>To secure equipment and prevent it from submerging or going down to the bottom of the sea, Hammar COR can give buoyancy and protection by inflating a chamber or bladder. High Eye protects their crewless helicopter with the Hammar Inflator System if it goes down in the water.<\/p>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/www.higheye.com\/applications-and-missions\/\">Visit High Eye for more information.<\/a><\/p>\n\t\t\t\t<img decoding=\"async\" data-src=\"https:\/\/www.cmhammar.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/10\/240801-Trevor-Burd-Life-Jacket-16-2-scaled.jpg\" alt=\"240801 Trevor Burd Life Jacket-16-2\" itemprop=\"image\" height=\"1200\" width=\"1800\" title=\"240801 Trevor Burd Life Jacket-16-2\" onerror=\"this.style.display='none'\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB3aWR0aD0iMSIgaGVpZ2h0PSIxIiB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciPjwvc3ZnPg==\" class=\"lazyload\" style=\"--smush-placeholder-width: 1800px; --smush-placeholder-aspect-ratio: 1800\/1200;\" \/>\n<h3>\n\t\tAMERICA&#8217;S CUP\n\t<\/h3>\nThe life jackets worn by the America&#8217;s Magic team, designed by Helly Hansen, are equipped with our advanced Hammar COR inflator. This is a critical piece of technology that ensures superior performance and reliability in the toughest conditions.\n<p>As one of the most prestigious and demanding sailing competitions, the America&#8217;s Cup pushes both athletes and equipment to their absolute limits. With sailing speeds reaching extreme levels, safety remains a top priority.<\/p>\n\t<iframe title=\"COR for American Magic\" width=\"500\" height=\"281\" data-src=\"https:\/\/www.youtube.com\/embed\/xr_6na1ziHs?feature=oembed\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share\" referrerpolicy=\"strict-origin-when-cross-origin\" allowfullscreen src=\"data:image\/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB3aWR0aD0iMSIgaGVpZ2h0PSIxIiB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciPjwvc3ZnPg==\" class=\"lazyload\" data-load-mode=\"1\"><\/iframe>\n\t\t\t\t<img decoding=\"async\" data-src=\"https:\/\/www.cmhammar.com\/wp-content\/plugins\/bb-plugin\/img\/pixel.png\" alt=\"\" itemprop=\"image\" onerror=\"this.style.display='none'\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB3aWR0aD0iMSIgaGVpZ2h0PSIxIiB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciPjwvc3ZnPg==\" class=\"lazyload\" style=\"--smush-placeholder-width: 3px; --smush-placeholder-aspect-ratio: 3\/2;\" \/>\n<h3>\n\t\tPRODUCTS FOR EX-ZONES\n\t<\/h3>\n\t<p>ATEX and IECEx are certifications for equipment intended for use in potentially explosive atmospheres such as tankers (chemical, oil, and gas) operating at sea. Hammar has products for increasing safety on these vessels.<\/p>\n\t<a href=\"#modal1349681631\" data-toggle=\"modal\">\n    Read more  EX      <\/a>\n\t\t\t\t                          <h2>OUR EX-PRODUCTS<\/h2>\n                                <p>There are two different schemes for certifying equipment intended for use in potentially explosive atmospheres: IECEx and ATEX. Schemes are generally incorporated by classification societies&#8217; (such as DNVGL and Bureau Veritas) class rules making them mandatory to classed vessels. Flag state, cargo terminals, and cargo owners may set up their own regulations for potentially hazardous environments.\u00a0<h2>IECEx<a href=\"https:\/\/www.cmhammar.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/02\/IECEX.png\"><img decoding=\"async\" data-src=\"https:\/\/www.cmhammar.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/02\/IECEX-300x257.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"257\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB3aWR0aD0iMSIgaGVpZ2h0PSIxIiB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciPjwvc3ZnPg==\" class=\"lazyload\" style=\"--smush-placeholder-width: 300px; --smush-placeholder-aspect-ratio: 300\/257;\" \/><\/a><\/h2>The most common is the voluntary scheme for harmonization under IEC (International Electrotechnical Commission), the IECEx. Schemes are generally incorporated by classification societies&#8217; (such as DNVGL and Bureau Veritas) class rules making them mandatory to classed vessels. Flag-state, cargo terminals, and cargo owners may set up their own regulations for potentially hazardous environments.\u00a0The potentially hazardous environments are divided into zones that determine the level of protection needed for the respective zone&#8217;s equipment.<ul><li aria-level=\"1\">Zone 0 &#8211; Area in which an explosive gas atmosphere is present continuously or is present for long periods.<\/li><li aria-level=\"1\">Zone 1 &#8211; Area in which an explosive gas atmosphere is likely to occur in normal operation.<\/li><li aria-level=\"1\">Zone 2 &#8211; Area in which an explosive gas atmosphere is not likely to occur in normal operation. If it does, it is likely to do so only infrequently and will only exist for a short period. (IEC:1999(E)ELECTRICAL INSTALLATIONS IN SHIPS -Part 502: Tankers &#8211; Special features)<\/li><\/ul><h2>ATEX<\/h2><h2><a href=\"https:\/\/www.cmhammar.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/02\/Aufkleber_EX_explosionsgeschuetzt.jpg\"><img decoding=\"async\" data-src=\"https:\/\/www.cmhammar.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/02\/Aufkleber_EX_explosionsgeschuetzt-300x267.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"267\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB3aWR0aD0iMSIgaGVpZ2h0PSIxIiB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciPjwvc3ZnPg==\" class=\"lazyload\" style=\"--smush-placeholder-width: 300px; --smush-placeholder-aspect-ratio: 300\/267;\" \/><\/a><\/h2>The EU Directive 2014\/34\/EU, formally know as ATEX, does not apply to seagoing vessels and mobile offshore units together with equipment on board such as vessels or units. Ports, terminals, and flag states in the European Union are obliged to follow these regulations, which is why it is also applied to ships.For applications in these potentially hazardous environments, Hammar has developed and certified a range of products approved to ATEX and IECEx standards.<a href=\"https:\/\/www.cmhammar.com\/product-category\/ex\/\">Here you can find our range of EX products.<\/a><\/p>                              \n <h3>\n\t\tPRODUCTS FOR UNDERWATER APPLICATIONS\n\t<\/h3>\n\t<p>Hammar sees the potential area of promoting <b>Better Solutions for Safety at Sea<\/b> by using our product range and limiting time using divers or ROVs (Remotely Operated Vehicles). With vast knowledge in our area of competence, we can help you solve your underwater release.<\/p>\n\t\t\t\t<img decoding=\"async\" data-src=\"https:\/\/www.cmhammar.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/Cache-close-up-003-571x1024.jpg\" alt=\"Cache close up (003)\" itemprop=\"image\" height=\"1024\" width=\"571\" title=\"Cache close up (003)\" onerror=\"this.style.display='none'\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB3aWR0aD0iMSIgaGVpZ2h0PSIxIiB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciPjwvc3ZnPg==\" class=\"lazyload\" style=\"--smush-placeholder-width: 571px; --smush-placeholder-aspect-ratio: 571\/1024;\" \/>\n<h3>\n\t\tFeel free to contact us with any questions you may have on special applications.\n\t<\/h3>\n\t\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/www.cmhammar.com\/contact-us\/\" target=\"_self\" rel=\"noopener\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\tContact Us\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/a>\n\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>SPECIAL APPLICATIONS By combining, adapting, and developing technology, Hammar&#8217;s products are applicable to more areas for saving lives at sea. &nbsp; HAMMAR IN SPECIAL APPLICATIONS We continuously develop state-of-the-art products that correspond to our customers&#8217; demands. In collaboration with our customers, we design new products by unconventional and innovative thinking &#8211; products that increase safety&#8230;<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":2,"featured_media":0,"parent":0,"menu_order":0,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","template":"","meta":{"_acf_changed":false,"footnotes":""},"class_list":["post-4163","page","type-page","status-publish","hentry"],"acf":[],"yoast_head":"<!-- This site is optimized with the Yoast SEO plugin v26.7 - https:\/\/yoast.com\/wordpress\/plugins\/seo\/ -->\n<title>Special Applications - Hammar<\/title>\n<meta name=\"description\" content=\"Our Special Applications range is applied to our HRUs, Remote Release Systems, Inflators or special projects for your specific application\" \/>\n<meta name=\"robots\" content=\"index, follow, max-snippet:-1, max-image-preview:large, max-video-preview:-1\" \/>\n<link rel=\"canonical\" href=\"https:\/\/www.cmhammar.com\/special-applications\/\" \/>\n<meta property=\"og:locale\" content=\"en_US\" \/>\n<meta property=\"og:type\" content=\"article\" \/>\n<meta property=\"og:title\" content=\"Special Applications - Hammar\" \/>\n<meta property=\"og:description\" content=\"Our Special Applications range is applied to our HRUs, Remote Release Systems, Inflators or special projects for your specific application\" \/>\n<meta property=\"og:url\" content=\"https:\/\/www.cmhammar.com\/special-applications\/\" \/>\n<meta property=\"og:site_name\" content=\"Hammar\" \/>\n<meta property=\"article:modified_time\" content=\"2024-10-21T07:53:16+00:00\" \/>\n<meta property=\"og:image\" content=\"https:\/\/www.cmhammar.com\/wp-content\/plugins\/bb-plugin\/img\/pixel.png\" \/>\n<meta name=\"twitter:card\" content=\"summary_large_image\" \/>\n<script type=\"application\/ld+json\" class=\"yoast-schema-graph\">{\"@context\":\"https:\/\/schema.org\",\"@graph\":[{\"@type\":\"WebPage\",\"@id\":\"https:\/\/www.cmhammar.com\/special-applications\/\",\"url\":\"https:\/\/www.cmhammar.com\/special-applications\/\",\"name\":\"Special Applications - Hammar\",\"isPartOf\":{\"@id\